.TH "super" "1" "April 2026" ""
.SH NAME
\f[B]super\f[R] \(em process data with SuperSQL queries
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]super\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[B]\-c\f[R] \f[I]query\f[R]]
[\f[B]\-I\f[R] \f[I]query\-file\f[R] \&...]
[\f[I]file\f[R] \&...]
.PP
\f[B]super\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]args\f[R]
\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[CR]super\f[R] executes SuperSQL queries against files, HTTP/HTTPS/S3
URLs, and standard input, independent of a database storage layer.
When invoked without a sub\-command, the query engine runs detached from
any database.
Input paths may be filesystem paths, URLs, or \f[B]\-\f[R] for standard
input.
If no query is given, inputs are scanned and re\-serialized in the
format specified by \f[B]\-f\f[R].
If no input is specified, the query receives a single \f[B]null\f[R]
value.
.PP
Input format is detected automatically from file extensions or content.
The \f[B]line\f[R] format cannot be auto\-detected and must be specified
with \f[B]\-i line\f[R].
